# Project Roadmap - Eco-Adaptive AI (12 Months)

### Quarter 1: Research & Localization
- Field research in TTS (Mollo & Kolbano) to record local teacher accents for AI training.
- Development of the "Fatigue Logic" framework based on student commute distances.
- Initial hardware setup for IoT environmental sensors.

### Quarter 2: Core Engine Development
- Integration of OpenAI Whisper for offline transcription.
- Fine-tuning HuggingFace models for educational summarization in Indonesian/Local context.
- Building the "Resilience Mode" trigger (Logic that switches UI/UX based on climate data).

### Quarter 3: Pilot Testing & Edge Deployment
- Deployment of Edge AI servers in 5 pilot schools in TTS.
- Real-world testing with students walking >5 km.
- Collecting feedback on "Micro-Summary" effectiveness for exhausted students.

### Quarter 4: Optimization & Open Source Scale-up
- Refinement of AI models based on pilot data.
- Releasing full documentation for global use in other remote regions.
- Establishing data partnership with the Local Education Office.
